    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.15-16_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">15</fw>
                
                <p>On Reading "The Song of Hugh Glass". Today I rode the trails with one Hugh Glass Down winding rivers o'er the prairie grass. I thought of friends I've had in days gone by And was <unclear>made</unclear> happy just to think that I Had never been betrayed by one I loved. Today I crawled his crawl &#8212; wit<del/><add>h</add> pain I moved, And I could even taste the <unclear>very</unclear> taste there with John Neihardt's hero on the waste, of dog meat and of putrid buffalo.</p>
                
                <p>His is a knack that I will never know of <unclear/> episodes and trials grim. It may be sinful, still I envy him.</p>
                
            </div1>
            
            
